tags.description: Woodbourne Green Park is a triangular shaped parcel located where Whipp Road meets Paddington Road. The park features a rock with a historical marker placed by the Centerville Historical Society in 1971.

tags.description: Forest Walk Park is a nature park with trails and wooded areas. The park can be accessed from Forest Brook Boulevard and Deer Run Road. Play equipment with climbers, belt swings and infant swings located near each entrance.
tags.name: Forest Walk Park

tags.description: A neighborhood park with a large open area for sports and a wooded area and stream for exploring. A grill and picnic tables make this an ideal spot for lunch. Play equipment was updated in 2016 and includes slides, climbers, belt swings and infant swings.
tags.name: Beechwood Springs Park

tags.description: The park provides a resting spot for bicyclists traveling the multi-use trail on the shared sidewalk along Spring Valley Pike. It is located in the McEwen Woods neighborhood, just west of McEwen Road.
